@startuml HealthBank_Login_2FA_Sequence
!theme plain
skinparam sequenceArrowColor #2C76BF
skinparam sequenceLifeLineBorderColor #595959
skinparam sequenceParticipantBorderColor #1A1A2E
skinparam sequenceParticipantBackgroundColor #EBF4FF
skinparam sequenceGroupBorderColor #AAAAAA
skinparam shadowing false
autoactivate off

title HealthBank — Login with 2FA Sequence

actor       "User"         as U
participant "Flutter App"  as APP
participant "FastAPI\n/api/v1/auth" as API
database    "MySQL"        as DB

== Standard Login ==

U -> APP : Enter email + password\n[Submit]
APP -> API : POST /api/v1/auth/login\n{ email, password }
API -> DB  : SELECT AccountID, PasswordHash, RoleID,\n       IsActive, MustChangePassword,\n       LockoutUntil, FailedAttempts\nFROM Auth JOIN AccountData
DB --> API : account row

alt Account is locked
  API --> APP : 403 { "locked": true, retry_after }
  APP --> U   : "Account locked — contact administrator"

else Invalid credentials
  API -> DB  : UPDATE Auth SET FailedAttempts = FailedAttempts + 1
  API --> APP : 401 Unauthorized
  APP --> U   : "Incorrect email or password"

else Valid credentials, 2FA disabled
  API -> DB  : INSERT INTO Sessions (TokenHash, AccountID, ExpiresAt)
  DB --> API : session created
  API --> APP : 200 { role, must_change_password }\nSet-Cookie: session_token=<hash>; HttpOnly; SameSite=Lax
  APP --> U   : Redirect to role dashboard

else Valid credentials, 2FA enabled
  API --> APP : 200 { requires_2fa: true, challenge_token }
  APP --> U   : Show TOTP prompt

  == 2FA Challenge ==

  U -> APP : Enter 6-digit TOTP code
  APP -> API : POST /api/v1/2fa/verify\n{ challenge_token, code }
  API -> DB  : SELECT TotpSecret (encrypted)\nFROM TwoFactor WHERE AccountID = ?
  DB --> API : encrypted secret
  API -> API : Decrypt secret\nValidate TOTP code (±30s window)

  alt TOTP code valid
    API -> DB  : INSERT INTO Sessions\nUPDATE Auth SET FailedAttempts = 0
    DB --> API : session created
    API --> APP : 200 { role, must_change_password }\nSet-Cookie: session_token=<hash>; HttpOnly
    APP --> U   : Redirect to role dashboard

  else TOTP code invalid (rate-limited: 5 attempts / 60s)
    API --> APP : 401 { "invalid_code": true }
    APP --> U   : "Incorrect code — try again"
  end
end

== Temporary Password Enforcement ==

note over APP, API
  If must_change_password = true, Flutter router
  redirects to /change-password before any
  other route is accessible
end note

@enduml
